       PyTorch Image Processing

1) Copy the file

pytorch-multigpu.py

to your working directory (preferably on the /blue filesystyem).

2) Load PyTorch

ml purge
ml ngc-pytorch/1.11.0
ml

3) Run the example on 1 Gpu

time python pytorch-multigpu.py --num-gpus 1

and then on 2 GPUs

time python pytorch-multigpu.py --num-gpus 2

and compare the image processing speeds.

